Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop diagonally into
large 3cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

When hot, add the courgette and cook until starting to go golden, ~{4-5%minutes}
total. Turn only every couple of mins.

Meanwhile, lay the @British chicken breasts{2} onto a large #baking tray{},
sprinkle over half the @curry powder mix{1%sachet}, drizzle with oil and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast the chicken on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through,
~{25-30%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the courgette has started to go golden, reduce the heat to medium, add the
@butter{20%grams} and remaining curry powder mix to the #pan. Cook for
~{1-2%minutes} more.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%grams} and @water{50%milliliters} for the
sauce, then cover with a #lid{} (or foil). Allow to cook until tender,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @lentils{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Stir the lentils, @korma curry paste{50%grams}, @soured cream{75%grams} and
@sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce through the braised vegetables. Bring to the boil,
then remove from the heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Just before everything's ready, reheat the lentils, adding a splash more water if
you feel it needs it.

Once the chicken is cooked drizzle over the @honey{1%tbsp}, then thinly slice
widthways.

Share the curried lentils and braised courgette between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with the sliced chicken and sprinkle over the @toasted flaked almonds{15%grams}
to finish. Enjoy!